<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Fiona Falkiner is pregnant with her first child with fiancée, Hayley Willis.</p>

<p>And on Wednesday, the 37-year-old shared a joyous photo cradling her growing baby bump to social media.</p>

<p>'Two bras and shapewear holding in the bump,' Fiona claimed as she smiled radiantly for the mirror selfie.</p>

<p>She's glowing: Pregnant Fiona Falkiner cradles her baby bump in a joyous photo as she jokes it's taking 'two bras and shapewear' to hold herself in</p>

<p>Fiona placed her hand on her lower stomach, as she showed off her nude undergarments while wearing a pair of denim shorts.</p>

<p>Earlier this week, Fiona shared her baby's first sonogram with her followers on Instagram, and thanked them for their support.</p>

<p>Taking to social media platform, the former Biggest Loser host kept things simple as she showed off the image off her growing baby against a blue background. </p>

<p>Baby joy! Fiona is pregnant with her first child with fiancée, Hayley Willis (left)</p>

<p>Love: The Biggest Loser's Fiona Falkiner shared her baby's first sonogram and thanked fans for their support after she announced she is pregnant with partner Hayley Willis</p>

<p>Praise: 'We are over the moon, we can't even describe it. We're blown away by all your beautiful messages,' Fiona said. 'Thank you all so much'</p>

<p>'Had a scan today... head to whattheivfpodcast see our little Emby jumping around,' Fiona wrote.  </p>

<p>Fiona announced their baby joy in an Instagram post on Monday, sharing a photo of Hayley cradling her bump.</p>

<p>'It's official, our little family will be gaining a member. Baby Falkiner will be joining us in 2021,' the model wrote. </p>

<p>'We are so excited about this new chapter of being mums together and giving this little bundle all the love in the world! Thank you to everyone who sent us prayers and baby dust. It worked!' she added.</p>

<p>Nine journalist Hayley, who proposed to Fiona in April 2019 after 10 months of dating, also posted the same image to Instagram with her own heartfelt caption.</p>

<p>'It's official, our little family will be gaining a member. Baby Falkiner will be joining us in 2021,' model Fiona shared with her fans</p>

<p>'We did it, my love. It's hard to put into words how incredibly proud I am of you. All of our family dreams are finally coming true,' she began. </p>

<p>'Feeling incredibly blessed and absolutely over the moon to begin this new chapter of our lives. I can't wait to be a mumma with you!'</p>

<p>'Baby Falkiner due March 2021!' she added.</p>

<p>Baby bliss: 'Feeling incredibly blessed and absolutely over the moon to begin this new chapter of our lives. I can't wait to be a Mumma with you!' Hayley wrote on her Instagram page</p>

<p>'Fi is going first because she is older': In an interview with The Daily Telegraph not long ago, Hayley said she hopes to carry a baby once Fiona has given birth</p>

<p>Not long ago, Fiona spoke about her 'traumatic' and 'lonely' IVF journey in an interview with The Daily Telegraph. </p>

<p>She told the newspaper: 'It is you and your body against all odds. Women don't really talk about it until after the fact. It can be really quite traumatic.'</p>

<p>Hayley also revealed that she, too, hopes to carry a baby once Fiona has given birth.</p>

<p>'Fi is going first because she is older. I really want to carry a bub too but Fi will go first just because of the body clock on fertility, so her going first is best,' she said. </p>

<p>Happily ever after! Fiona and Hayley announced their engagement in April 2019, after 10 months of dating</p>
